### Instrument gRPC Server Handlers in Node.js Agent

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This update enhances the Node.js agent by adding instrumentation for gRPC server handlers. It supports unary, client-streaming, server-streaming, and bidirectional streaming. This allows New Relic to monitor the performance and transaction context of incoming gRPC requests.

```javascript
// Example of instrumented gRPC server handler (conceptual):
const grpc = require('@grpc/grpc-js');
const server = new grpc.Server();
server.addService(MyService.service, {
  myMethod: call => { /* ... */ }
});
server.bindAsync('0.0.0.0:50051', grpc.ServerCredentials.createInsecure(), () => {
  server.start();
});

// The New Relic agent will now track requests handled by this server.
```

