### Configure Instrumentation Enabled State in Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

Allows disabling specific package instrumentation via configuration. This is useful for performance tuning or avoiding conflicts. It modifies the `config.instrumentation.<pkg-name>.enabled` setting.

```javascript
{
  "instrumentation": {
    "@hapi/hapi": {
      "enabled": false
    }
  }
}
```

