### Instrument Fastify Routes in New Relic Node.js Agent

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This describes how Fastify routes are instrumented by the New Relic Node.js agent, specifically by wrapping the `addHook` method. This ensures that Fastify v2 and v3 routes are properly tracked for performance monitoring. The instrumentation is now generally available (GA).

```javascript
// Example of how addHook might be wrapped (conceptual)
const addHook = fastifyInstance.addHook;
fastifyInstance.addHook = function(...args) {
  // New Relic instrumentation logic here
  return addHook.apply(this, args);
};
```

