### Record Application Log Event - Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet demonstrates how to record application log events using the `newrelic.recordLogEvent()` method. It shows how to include a simple message and level, as well as how to serialize an error object within the log event. This functionality is useful for forwarding application logs and performing local decorating.

```javascript
newrelic.recordLogEvent({ message: 'hello world', level: 'info' })

```

```javascript
const error = new Error('testing errors'); 
newrelic.recordLogEvent({ message: 'error example', level: 'error', error })

```

