### Capture and Obfuscate SQL Statements - Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

Starting from v10.0.0, the Node.js agent defaults to capturing and obfuscating SQL statements. This change impacts how SQL queries are stored and displayed in New Relic, enhancing security by masking sensitive data while still allowing for performance analysis.

```javascript
config.transaction_tracer.record_sql: "obfuscated"
```

