### Execute Instrumentation in Segment Context with Node.js Agent

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This illustrates how to execute instrumentation functions within the context of a segment descriptor in the New Relic Node.js agent. This is achieved by providing a function within the `inContext` key of the segment descriptor passed to the record method.

```javascript
shim.record(
  segmentDescriptor,
  {
    inContext: function(segment) {
      // Code to execute within the segment's context
      // 'segment' here refers to the segment descriptor
    }
  }
);
```

