### Instrumenting Generic Modules with newrelic.instrument() in Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

The `newrelic.instrument()` method, along with `Shim`, allows for the instrumentation of generic Node.js modules. This is useful for libraries like connection pools or task schedulers that do not have specialized instrumentation. It requires the `newrelic` module to be imported.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

// Example usage with a hypothetical task scheduler module
const taskScheduler = require('my-task-scheduler');

newrelic.instrument(taskScheduler, function() {
  // Instrumentation logic here
  // This function will be called when the module is loaded
  console.log('Task scheduler module instrumented');
});
```

